summary:
Jon Snow 8x11 Graphite on printer paper
Lately I've gone through some changes and they are difficult but my art (and family) are...
body:
Jon Snow 8x11 Graphite on printer paper

Lately I’ve gone through some changes and they are difficult but my art (and family) are pulling me through. This is a drawing of Jon Snow; I usually work with charcoal, but decided to do a study using graphite. Scanning the drawing is fine but after burnishing into the paper it was so shiny. Anyway this took me about 6 hours to finish. On and off. I work a lot, but I’m planning on doing more. I did it on printer paper so I wouldn’t fall in love in attempts to make a masterpiece and to instead just learn something without destroying my own confidence. I’m a harsh critic. Threw him into photoshop blurred the background and flipped him. I see my faults in this piece, but you only learn by implementing them in the next drawing and then the next and so on. Sorry for that tacky ass DW in the corner. I’ll create a signature soon.

Over and out.

D.W.
